# Cursor Rules

This directory contains all the coding rules and guidelines for the project, organized into separate files for better maintainability.

## File Structure

- `role-and-expertise.mdc` - Role definition and expertise areas
- `core-principles.mdc` - Core development principles
- `objective.mdc` - Project objectives and goals
- `project-overview.mdc` - Project structure and tech stack
- `code-implementation-guidelines.mdc` - Code implementation rules
- `coding-standards.mdc` - TypeScript, React patterns, and coding standards
- `accessibility.mdc` - Accessibility guidelines and checklist
- `state-management.mdc` - State management patterns (Zustand, nuqs, TanStack Query)
- `styling.mdc` - Tailwind CSS and styling guidelines
- `testing.mdc` - Testing strategies and tools
- `development-methodology.mdc` - Development methodology and process
- `code-style-and-structure.mdc` - Code style and file organization
- `advanced-typescript.mdc` - Advanced TypeScript patterns
- `performance-optimization.mdc` - Performance optimization techniques
- `code-quality.mdc` - Code quality standards
- `common-patterns.mdc` - Common development patterns
- `git-workflow.mdc` - Git workflow and code review checklist
- `notes.mdc` - General notes and reminders

## Usage

These rules are automatically loaded by Cursor IDE. They guide AI-assisted development to ensure consistency, quality, and best practices throughout the codebase.

